19/04/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Arsonists attacked the offices of two former ministers in Athens on Monday (April 18th), causing minor damage but no injuries. Police say a homemade device exploded outside the office of former Tourism Minister Fanny Palli Petralia first. A bit later, a similar bomb failed to explode in the office of former Public Works Minister Vasso Papandreou in the same building. No group has assumed responsibility. (Nafthemporiki, Ta Nea, Proto Thema - 19/04/11)
